Use \code{w_var()} when:
\itemize{
\item You need variance for further calculations (e.g., pooled variance, F-tests)
\item You want to compare variability across groups with proper weighting
\item Your analysis formulas require variance rather than SD
\item You need SPSS-compatible weighted variance values
}

For reporting purposes, \code{\link{w_sd}} is usually preferred because
the standard deviation is in the same units as the original variable.
